$ VBA statement: declare
@ declare

`declare` is needed to locate and a procedure or function in a → Windows/development/Portable-Executable/DLL[DLL]. In order to be callable from VBA,
this procedure or function needs to have the → development/languages/C-C-plus-plus/calling-convention#stdcall[stdcall] calling convention.

Don't confuse `declare` with → development/languages/VBA/language/statements/dim[`dim`].

sa:

  → development/languages/VBA/Calling-DLLs[Accessing and calling DLLs from VBA]

  → development/languages/VBA/language/statements
